Name: Talk to Papa
Description: Now that [n33] is awake, he would like you to check on [n37]. Please go to see [n29] and check whether or not [n37] is still asleep.

Name: All About Ambience
Description: [n29] is in need of help! With [n37] asleep, there is no one to help around the coffee house. [n29] would like you to collect 10 [i1410] for him to decorate the shop. [i1410] are in the [p37].

Name: A Fixer-Upper
Description: Now that the shop is smelling nice, it is time to fix the coffee house up! [n29] 13 [i1212] and 25 [i1205] from Mulberry Trees in [p36] and 10 [i1211] from Kaolit Trees in [p32].

Name: Under Renovation
Description: [n29] is in need of help! With [n37] asleep, there is no one to help around the coffee house. [n29] would like you to collect 8 [i1410] for him to decorate the shop. [i1410] are in the [p37]. He also needs a couple of things to fix up the shop such as 8 [i1212] and 8 [i1205]. You can get these from Mulberry Trees in [p36].

Name: All Brand New
Description: The [i574] and [i575] got dirty with all the construction going on. Go to [n39] and pick up 10 [i574] and 5 [i575] for the Coffee Shop. She is located at [p204].

Requirements.Text: qflag 0 "Go to [n39] and pick up the items "
qflag 0 "Go to [n39] and pick up the items "

Name: The Missing Order
Description: The coffee shop is all fixed up! There is still something missing. [n29] ordered some [i553] a while back but it never showed up. Talk to [n30] regarding this matter. She's located in [p206] in [p9].

Name: Plate Brigade
Description: [n30] is so busy that she completely forgot about [n29]'s order. She would like you to help her collect some [i1001] and [i1002] in the [p34] or [p35]. Return to her after you collect 15 [i1001] and 20 [i1002].

Name: Right on Track
Description: The [i553] are finally finished! [n30] would like you to bring it back to [p202]. Talk to [n29] and give these [i553] to him.

Name: Waking Purin
Description: Thanks to your help, [p202] is ready for business. The only thing left is to wake up [n37]! The last person to see him awake was [n32]. Please go talk to him to see if he can provide any clues to this mystery.

Name: Bramble Surprise
Description: There is a breakthrough in [n37]'s case! It seems  [n32] discovered a [i518] that might hold clues to waking up [n37]. The [m84] claimed it as its own. Retrieve [i518] and bring it to [n28] for inspection.

Name: Pieces of the Puzzle
Description: [n28] has figured out the mystery behind this key! Bring it to [p201] and try to open the door.

Name: Purin's Coffee
Description: You've finally met [n37] but he is very groggy and not in any condition to cooperate. He needs some coffee! It is time for you to leap into action. Talk to him again to make some coffee!

Requirements.Text: qflag 0 "Make 12 cups of coffee in mini game"

Name: Order from Purin's Mama
Description: [n31] would like you to help her make [i1785]! In order to do so, you must collect 10 [i5022] from [p31] and bring her 10 [i1832].

Name: Another Order from Mama
Description: [n31] has a little bit of honey from the [i1785] she made. She wants to teach you how to make [i1835] with it. However, she doesn't have all the ingredients. Collect 20 [i1406] from [p36] and bring it back to [n31].

Name: Jammin' with Mama
Description: [n31] is going to teach you how to make another dish! Collect 20 [i1409] from [p36] or [p37].

Name: To Merry Ol' London
Description: [n37] is thankful that you woke him up! Now that he's back, he'll be able to help his parents again. He would like you to deliver a letter to [n35] in [p10] for him. Go see [n35] in [p10].

Name: Peppy's Request
Description: [n135] grain's supply is running low! He would like you to collect 20 [i1412] from [p37]. Return to him once you gather the [i1412].

Name: In Need of Comfort
Description: [n135] would like to have some [i5009]. Collect 10 [i5009] for her. The [m5] is located in [p31].

Name: Helping the Gals
Description: [n36] would like you to go see [n30] regarding the whereabouts of [n33]. She is located at [p206] in [p9].

Name: Learn to Forge
Description: [n32] would like you to forge materials for him! Get him 10 [i514] and 5 [i585]. If you don't have the guides, they can be purchased from [n38].

Name: Business is Rolling
Description: Thanks to you, [n32] is doing great with his new business. Now he needs you to make him 10 [i589] and 6 [i590]. You can obtain instructions on how to make them from [n38].

Name: A Big Order
Description: [n32] is in need of your help again! [n30] made a big order of [i591] and [n32] would like you to make 7 of them for him. If you are missing ingredients, try to look for it among the merchants.

Name: The Last Job
Description: [n32] thinks it's going to rain in Sanrio Land soon. He would like you to make 5 [i2004] for him to sell when it does rain. Please hurry before it rains!

Name: Merry Old London
Description: Welcome to [p10]! [n144], [n41] and [n49] have fallen into deep sleep and the people of [p10] are all out of ideas. [n35] thinks [n43] knows more about these mysteries. Please talk to him at once.

Name: Cutting Corners
Description: [n43] thinks you'll need a new pair of scissors before proceeding with your adventure. Collect 2 [i594], 2 [i516], 1 [i593], and 10 [i5110]. You might have to travel back to [p39] and for the [i5110] and the [i1008] but it's definitely worth it! The [i1213] will be found in [p38] and rest can be bought from the merchants.

Name: Digging Deeper
Description: [n43] still thinks you're not yet ready to tackle the mystery in [p10]. This time, please collect 1 [i594], 1 [i593], 5 [i516], 10 [i5055] from [m25] in [p43] and 10 [i5120] from [m32] in [p41]. Return to him once you're done with his request.

Name: New Toys
Description: You're almost prepared for your tough road ahead. This time, [n43] feels that your wand is not potent enough to handle all the rowdy monsters beyond [p10]. He has promised to make you a new wand but you will need to get all the materials. Please make 10 [i534] and 10 [i535] and gather 5 [i1012] from the Coal in [p39].

Name: More Information
Description: [n43] has a lead on [n49]'s situation. Not long ago, [n49] was perfectly fine and was even gathering flowers for [n47] in [p41]. Now, he's sleeping inside [p215] and they can't get to him because it's locked! Please head to [p41] and talk to [n56] as soon as possible.

Name: Bait and Switch
Description: [n56] did see a key! However, the monsters nearby carried it away. Usually, [i10108] are enough to offer to them but lately, they've grown tired of it. It's time for a new approach! Please harvest 10 [i10126], 10 [i10101] and 10 [i10115] in your farm.

Name: Daniel's Plea
Description: [n56] found the key and is positive that this will open up the door in [p215]. Please use the key right away and wake [n49] up!

Name: Super Secret Tech
Description: The monsters have struck again! This time, [n35]'s [i10158] were stolen and now, he can't grow new ones in time. He needs to make his super secret drink but will need your help. Please bring him 15 [i10158] and 15 [i1713].

Name: Repairing What's Broken
Description: [n35]'s pot has shattered! Collect 10 [i1007], 2 [i1015] and 2 [i1017] from Stone Piles in [p40].

Name: Doughnut Touch!
Description: [n35] feels there's still something missing from his drink. He thinks that adding [n41]'s famous [i1787] might do the job. Return to him once you have found that special doughnut.

Name: Cherry Picking
Description: Everyone in [p10] is so worried at recent events that all they want to eat is comfort food - but the comfort food has run out! Bring [n42] 10 [i10115] because he's all out of ingredients to cook.

Name: Extra Hands
Description: [n42] needs extra hands. Help him by cooking 3 [i1782]. Give them to him as soon as possible.

Name: Extra Hands Once Again
Description: The orders keep coming and [n42] needs help more than ever. This time, a huge batch of orders for [i1777] came in and [n42] will need your culinary skills once again. Please cook 3 [i1777] and them to [n42] at once!

Name: Sous Chef and Mentor
Description: With the flow of orders slowing down, [n42] can now focus on unlocking [n41]'s house. Before [n41] fell asleep, [n42] was given the key to his mentor's house. However, when sous chef [n42] was gathering [i1421] in [p40], he must have dropped it. Talk to [n52] in [p40] and find out if he saw anything.

Name: Food for Thought
Description: [n52] found something shiny but is extremely hungry and a wee bit woozy and can't seem to think straight until he has a bite to eat. He wants you to try out his new recipe books and see if it's any good. Please bring him [i1806] and 5 [i1791].

Name: Mentor's Doughnut
Description: [n41] is awake again and would like to show his appreciation by sharing his famous [i8425] with you. Since he's been asleep for so long all his ingredients have spoiled. Gather all of the ingredients on the list and return to him so he can show you how to make the doughnuts.

Name: Mentor's Burger
Description: [n41] is up to his neck in food orders, which have piled up while he was sleeping. Make a big juicy [i1764] using the recipe and deliver it to [n85].

Name: Mentor's Salad
Description: The next order [n41] needs to fill is for a [i1748]. Gather the ingredients, follow the recipe and deliver the [i1748] to [n44].

Name: Mentor's Fruit Tea
Description: [n41] would like something to drink while he's busy cooking. Help him quench his thirst with a delicious glass of [i1727].

Name: Shhh... It's a Surprise!
Description: Thanks to you, [n49] is now awake! He would like you to help him gather materials for his secret present for [n47]. Find the materials and bring him 20 [i1419] from the Sungrass in [p44] and 20 [i1424] from the Black Nightshade in [p44] and give it back to [n49].

Name: Not Good Enough
Description: [n49] needs some wood for his secret project but it seems his axe isn't strong enough. Talk to [n43] to see if he has a better axe.

Name: Hacking Away
Description: [n49] needs special wood to make [n47]'s gift. [n43] recommends that you collect materials for a new axe before anything else. Please gather 10 [i1218] from the caterpillar trees in [p38] and make 2 [i1815], 1 [i594], 1 [i593] and 3 [i516].

Name: Maybe Something Special?
Description: With your new strong axe, go collect special wood for [n49]'s secret project.  Gather 10 [i1229] from Hedgehog Vine in the [p42], 10 [i1233] from Goat Bamboo in [p44] and 5 [i1227] from Big Wind Bell Tree in [p41].

Name: Entering the Stadium
Description: [n85] seems to have found a way to open [p214]. All he needs are his tools. He thinks [n57]'s might have them. You should visit [n57] in the [p42].

Name: The Search for Pyrodon
Description: The [m99] in [p44] took off with [i638]. Go get it back and then bring them back to [n57] for a reward.

Name: Pyrodon Sends his Regards
Description: Now that you have [i638], take it back to [n85] so that he can put the keys together.

Name: The Frog and the Ball
Description: Now that [n144] is awake he really, really wants to play soccer again with [n85]. Unfortunately, his soccer ball is a write-off: deflated and with holes in it. Bring him the materials he asks for so that he can make another ball.

Name: Keroppi's Goal Shootout
Description: Help [n144] practice his Goalie skills!

Requirements.Text: qflag 0 "Beat Keroppi in Keroppi's Goal Shootout"

Name: Kicking off the Season
Description: After playing soccer with [n85], [n144] thinks it's about time that they start a soccer team to compete for the Kitty Football Cup! Talk to [n85], [n86], [n89], [n92] and [n88] to see if they want to join.

Name: Communication Breakdown
Description: [n85] is thrilled about the new soccer team and wants to let all his friends know. Too bad his cell phone battery is dry... [n86] has an extra but he is afraid [n85] will break it. Give [n86] 12 [i1787] and he might change his mind.

Name: A Powerful Gift
Description: [n86] wants to thank [n85] for the [i1787]s by giving him a [i532]. Bring it back to [n85] for him.

Name: Burryball Bonanza
Description: The soccer team will need more Burryballs to practice. Please bring [n85] 6 [i592], 20 [i1235], and 10 [i510] so that he can make them.

Name: Piece of Cake!
Description: Looks like [n46] forgot the dessert for dinner... Please help [n45] make 2 [i1719]s.

Name: Rounding Up the Troops
Description: It's time for dinner but everyone's out and about! Please talk to [n48], [n43] and [n44] to remind them about dinner and talk to [n45] when you're finished.

Name: The Sorry Sweater
Description: After forgetting to bring dessert home, [n46] needs to make it up to [n45]. Please make a [i1836] and bring it back to [n46].

Name: The Moose-t Amazing Gag!
Description: [n46] has an idea for a funny gag involving a [i9986]. Make a [i9986] for this wacky old man.

Name: It's a Cook Off!
Description: [n42] thinks he has what it takes to win in a cook off against [n41]. Help get the ingredients ready for the competition.

Name: Tally the Votes
Description: Now that the judges have tasted the dishes, tally up their votes and get back to [n42] with the results. The judges are: [n43], [n44], [n45] and [n46].

Name: Anthony's Split Slacks
Description: [n43] seems to have ripped his pants beyond all hope of repair. Help [n44] make new [i1837].

Name: Patchy Pants
Description: It looks like the pants [n44] made were a bit on the small side and they ripped the moment [n43] tried them on!  Gather some more [i592], [i510] and a [i595] for [n44] to fix them.

Name: No More Paint?
Description: [n43] is working on a new painting but he seems to have run out of [i598], [i599] and [i600]. Please help him make more so he can finish it.

Name: Ouch! My Feet!
Description: After the last dance competition that [n49] participated in, his feet have been a bit sore. Please make him a pair of [i1838].

Name: Handy Helper
Description: [n43] just got a shiny new door for his house. Help him get ready to put it up by bringing him 20 [i596], 10 [i597], 35 [i5125], 1 [i5128], 35 [i5062] and 1 [i5107].

Name: Tea Time!
Description: [n35] needs to restock his cupboards but before he can do so, he needs 20 [i10157] and 20 [i10156].

Name: In a Pickle
Description: [n35] needs to make some pickled veggies for an upcoming picnic. Help him out by bringing him 20 [i10134] and 10 [i10125].

Name: Wonderful Watermelons
Description: After making all of those [i1746]s, [n35] could really go for a refreshing treat.  Bring him 10 [i10102].

Name: Keroppi's Goal Shootout
Description: Help [n144] practice his goalie skills!

Name: Parisian Blues
Description: Your friends [n67] and [n68] are in [p11] to look for their friend, [n72], because she didn't reply to the letter they sent a while back. Now, they're hungry and lost in a city they're not familiar with! They need a brave adventurer to search [p11] for [n72] and see if she's fine.

Name: Cookie Cutter
Description: [n72] is happy that her friends are in [p11]. She would like to make a batch of delicious [i1792] for them but she doesn't have enough materials. She needs you to collect 15 [i10136] and make 10 [i1835]. Return to her when you have the needed materials.

Name: A Friend Found
Description: [n72] wants to make her friends stop worrying about her. Take her letter and 8 [i689] and bring them to [n67] to make them enjoy their stay in [p11].

Name: Perfecting Your Craft
Description: [n72] is impressed by your cooking skills and suggested that you should pay [n70] a visit in order to learn more about cooking. You should bring her 5 [i1792] so she'll see how good a chef you are.

Name: Mail Fail
Description: [n67] is worried about the mailman, [n75]. There has been no mail delivery for days, suggesting that something has happened to the mailman.  It would be wise to visit [n69], [n75]'s assistant, and try to find out what happened to Sanrio Land's ever-so-dependable mailman.

Name: Mail Trails
Description:
Mail is overflowing in [p11]! [n69] needs you to 
deliver [i525] to [n64], [n70] and [n74] and [n72].

Name: Further Mail Trails
Description: Now that all the excess mail in [p11] has been sorted out, [n69]  needs you to travel to [p10], [p9] and [p8]. Deliver the letters to [n49] and [n41] in [p10], [n36] and [n37] in [p9] and [n112] and [n104] in [p8]. Return to [n69] when you have completed all deliveries.

Name: A Cryptic Request
Description: A strange letter has been discovered with some mysterious instructions. The scribbled handwriting is difficult to read, but it says: "You can find the key on A____os. It's one of the special monsters recognizable by their different coloring). You can find it in ___isty_____d." Travel all over Sanrio Land, find  this monster, and retrieve the key. You should be able to distinguish the special monster from the rest of its kind.

Name: Twins' Letter
Description: [n75] is back on his feet and ready to resume his duties. He believes the Little Twin Stars were the ones who wrote the mystery letter that led to his awakening. Go find them and see if it's true!

Requirements.Text: "Find and Talk to Little Twin Stars"

Name: An Old Box
Description: [n70] stumbled upon a box that belongs to [n71], but it's locked. [n73] is the perfect person if you're looking for someone to open that dirty old box. It could provide a way to wake up [n77] and her Papa.

Name: Taking Extra Steps
Description: [n73] can't find the key to open the box but he has another way. You will need to go to [p47] and collect [i1043]. You will also need to make [i535] and a [i595]. Return to [n73] once you've collected all the need materials.

Name: A Proud Owner
Description: [n73] wants to teach you how to properly take care of your cherished companion, your pet. Your pet can raise the attributes of your character (e.g. Energy, Energy Drain, harvesting speed) as well as enhancing your inventory to let you store more items. You can gain pet cards by putting monsters to sleep or you can buy them from pet shops. When your pets are following you, you'll need to feed and pet them so they can gain EXP. When pets earn enough EXP to level up, their basic attribute will be upgraded. Try to treat them well. Your pet is your faithful companion on your journeys in Sanrio Land!

Requirements.Text: "Listen to [n73]'s lesson and learn how to treat your pet"

Name: A Sticky Situation
Description: [n73]'s [i84] supply for his farm is running significantly low. Using your newfound knowledge of pet care, collect 15 [i85] from your pet and return to [n73].

Name: Chow Time!
Description: Time to learn how to feed your pet. [n73] wants you to collect [i1406], [i517], [i5022], [i1409]. Use them to cook a couple of [i1738].

Name: Melody's Red Hood
Description: The tattered, red hood you found inside [n71]'s box is actually an old hood of [n77]'s made by her grandma. This hood is a memento of sorts for the family of [n77] and her grandma would like to patch it up again. She will need [i641], [i1814], and [i629] bring them to her as soon as you collect them all.

Name: The Key and the Veggies
Description: [n74] found a key inside [n77]'s red cap, and she thinks that this is the key that could wake up [n71]. Before that, she wants you to collect [i10145], [i10133], [i10136], [i517] and [i1711]. Take the vegetables and the key to [n70].

Name: Waking Up Papa
Description: [n70] thinks that the key found inside [n77]'s old hood will open the doors of [p221]. She also thinks that cooking up a batch of [i1749] will be a nice surprise for [n71] when he wakes up.

Name: New-School Tools
Description: [n71] is awake and needs to get back to his gardening. But it looks like all of his tools have been stolen! Papa needs your help rebuilding his tools, starting with a [i29]. Collect the necessary materials.

Name: New-School Tools Again
Description: Now [n71] needs a new pickaxe. Get the materials on the list and he'll show you how to make a [i18].

Name: New-School Tools Once More
Description: [n71] needs to make one more tool, a pair of [i8013]. Once again, help him gather the materials and he'll teach you how to make the tool.

Name: A Package Found
Description: [n71] has found a package out in the garden but he can't tell whom it's for. The writing on the outside is smudged and hard to read, but there is a picture of a cherry on the package. Papa thinks it might belong to [n70] because she often orders ingredients for her baking.

Name: A Package in Distress
Description: The mystery package doesn't belong to [n70] after all. She thinks it might be for [n64] since he loves cherries. Check to see if he's expecting a package.

Name: Package-Go-Round
Description: The package apparently doesn't belong to [n64]. Time to go back to where it all started. Return the parcel to [n71].

Name: What? Again?
Description: [n71] is pretty sure the package isn't for him. Bring it back to [n70] one more time to see if she can figure it out.

Name: Purin's Gift
Description: [n70] finally decided to just open the parcel and see what's inside and what she found was a batch of cherry pudding. She needs you to go all over [p11] and share the [i1725] because she knows that's what [n37] would've wanted, being such a generous and kind boy. Deliver the cherry pudding to [n72], [n69], [n71], [n73] and [n74], [n64], [n67] and [n68]. Come back to [n70] once you delivered all the [i1725].

Name: A Sweet Surprise
Description: [n64] found a key inside his pudding. He has a feeling that this key will open the [p222]. Go and try wake up [n66]!

Name: Flower Arrangers!
Description: [n66] recalls how she ran into a monster in [p52] while she was picking flowers. It tried to cast a sleep spell on her but she managed to make it back to town before she fell asleep. However, she dropped her bag when the monster scared her. Go to [p52] to see if her bag is still there, and remember to pick some [i1444] and [i1440] for her while you're at it.

Name: Hungry Hungry Piano
Description: [n66] is hungry and is requesting some food. She'd like you to make [i1792], [i1763], and [i1749].

Name: Moving Up
Description: [n66] recalls finding a key that she believes will open the [p224] where My [n77] is locked away. Unfortunately, the bag was in the stolen by a monster! Before you set out to retrieve the bag, go see [n73]. He'll show you how to make a new wand that will help you in your quest.

Name: A New Wand Awaits You
Description: You need to help [n73] collect materials for a new magic wand. [n75] has a package for [n73] that needs to be picked up as well. Return to [n73] when you've collected [i646], [i647], [i5154], [i1042], [i517] and retrieved the package from [n75].

Name: Twin Stars Letter Express
Description: [n73]'s package is lost somewhere in the mail that has piled up while [n75] was asleep. He can't sort the mail out by himself, so he asks you to talk to the Little Twin Stars and see if they can help.

Requirements.Text:
qflag 0 "Finish the mini game and get 8000 
points"

Name: Prepping Up
Description: Before you go head out and face the big, bad monster, you will need to forge yourself a new pair of [i17502]. You will need to collect [i1031] and [i643]. A guide for [i643] can be bought in [p11] for you will need to make one as well. Return to [n74] when you've collected everything.

Name: When 2 Become 1
Description: With the two pet cards provided by [n73], visit the Pet Shop and breed a brand new pet. In order to breed a new pet, simply click on the Breed icon that is in the Pet Shop window. You then can find the name list on the right hand side of the Breed window, it'll list out names of new pets. You need to have both pet cards required, and both pets should have reached the level requirement to unlock the combination. You can also find the price for each new pet at the bottom of the window. Once you have chosen the new pet, you just need to press the "Breed it!" button, and the new pet card will appear in your inventory. Before using the new pet card, return to [n73] first and show it to him.

Name: It's in the Bag!
Description: You're all geared up and ready to go! The[m95] is in [p48] and still has [n66]'s bag; you will have to retrieve it and return it to [n66]. Be very careful of the [m95] because it is very powerful! When you get the bag back, pay [n66] a visit once again and return it to her.

Name: Waking Melody
Description: [n66] gave you the key to [p224]. Hurry over there and set [n77] free!

Requirements.Text: "Talk to [n77] and give her back the [i560]"

Name: A Secret Admirer
Description: Looks like [n64] wants to make [n47] a gift too. He needs special materials for his gift. Retrieve [i5149] from the [m46], [i5151] from the [m52] and [i5142] from the [m36].

Name: Feather Duster
Description: [n64] has finished his gift, now he wants to make a package for it. He needs you to collect a feather for him. Collect a rare feather from the [m69].

Name: aMAZEing
Description: [n76] wants you to memorize the whole of [p51]. You will need to fully explore the area so you can easily draw a map for it.

Name: Rocky Road
Description: There are so many rocks in [n148]'s garden that it's dangerous to walk there barefoot. [n148] needs your help to collect some materials for making shoes. Collect [i644], [i645], [i633], [i641] and [i5146].

Name: A Fresh Coat
Description: The walls inside the [p225] are old and dirty. [n76] wants to repaint but he doesn't have enough materials to make paints. Try to collect [i1817], [i515], [i517] and [i1016] for him.

Name: Another Layer of Paint
Description: Now [n76] needs another color of paint, purple. You can buy the guide from the shop.

Name: Wanted: Gorillo
Description: Looks like [n22] has a big problem. A naughty [m36] took his parcel, but he doesn't know which one took it. You may search [p52] to find out which [m36] took it.

Name: Cleaning the Contents
Description: All the things inside [n22]'s parcel were smeared with gunk! It's because of those naughty [m36]. [n22] is extremely upset. Can you help him? Try to complete the mini game by helping him to clean up the parcel contents.

Name: Road to Beijing
Description: [n102] told you that for some reason, Little Twin Stars have lost their powers. They can't fly and can't talk to Sun and Star anymore. Now they are just normal kids, and can't get back to [p22] because of the monsters. They're worrying about their friends in [p22]. Can you pay a visit to [p22] and see if their friends are fine.

Name: Parcel Delivery
Description: [n22] wants you to do him a favor. Take the [i551] to [p22] and give it to [n54].

Requirements.Text: "Take the [i551] to [p22] and give it to [n54]"

Name: Small Folk, Big Trees
Description: [n68] knows his friend, [n64], wants to build a new house. [n64] doesn't have time to collect the materials so he wants [n68] to help him but [n68] is too small for this task. Do him a favor and  collect the materials. Collect [i1258] from [i1801] found in your farm. [i1246] can be collected from Rainbow Tree in [p48].

Name: Oh, Before I Forget!
Description: [n68] forgot to tell you that there are two more kinds of wood that you need to collect. Will you help him again? The [i1247] can be chopped from Apple Trees while [i1263] can be gathered from Candy Tree in [p48].

Name: Intensive Research
Description: [n73] knows that the monsters in Sanrio Land are different and especially troublesome. He wants to research this matter and he needs someone to collect their pet cards. You need to travel to [p8] from [p9]. Return to [p8] and find [n27] to get more details about this research.

Name: Pet Hunt 1
Description: [n27]'s first task for you is to collect pet cards from monsters in areas near [p8] and [p9]. Once you've collected everything on the list, go back to [n73].

Name: Research Continue
Description: After researching [p8] and [p9], now Grandpa wants the sample of [p10]'s Monster. He wants you to find [n43] in [p10] to obtain further information.

Name: Pet Hunt 2
Description: [n43] wants you to search near [p10] and collect pet cards. Once all the cards are collected, return to [n73].

Name: Pet Hunt 3
Description: This time, [n73] wants you to do him one last favor. Go through the [p11] area and collect the required pet cards. Come back to [n73] when you've finished.

Name: Cooking Contest
Description: [n77] has decided to have a cooking contest with [n66]. She wants you to find a judge and she thinks her mother is the best choice. Talk to [n70] and see if she agrees.

Name: Melon Burgers!
Description: [n70] thinks that making [n77] and [n66] cook one recipe and see which one's more delicious is the best way to find out who the better chef is. She needs you to collect enough ingredients for the both of them so the contest can begin.

Name: Delicious Sandwiches
Description: It seems they're both equally good. [n70] thinks another dish is needed to decide which one is better. She needs your help again. Try to collect enough ingredients for [i1839].

Name: Mushroom Soup
Description: [n70] still can't choose whose cooking's best. She decides that making them cook Cream of [i1840] will finally decide the winner. Help [n70] collect enough ingredients for the contest.

Name: Draw-Go
Description: The contest ended in a draw! [n70] has concluded that [n77] and [n66] are equally good at cooking. She wants you to tell the result to both [n77] and [n66].

Name: Handle With Care
Description: There is a bunch of broken furniture in [p225] and [n76] needs some materials to fix it. Try to find 10 [i647] for him.

Name: Gold Digging
Description: Now [n76] needs [i1034] to repair the [p225]. You need to mine 20 [i1034] for him. You can get [i1034] from Electrum Rock located in [p50].

Name: Boot Up!
Description: [n148] said his friends like his [i15807]. He wants to make them all a pair. However, he can't do it by himself. Will you help him to make 3 [i15807]?

Name: Jumping Right In
Description: [n128] thinks that [n129] is one of the storied "sleepers" and is totally worried. Pay [n126] a visit because she knows someone who could help out with this situation.

Name: Deer-Gineer
Description: [n140], [n126]'s good friend, likes making lots of gadgets and other crazy things. He might have something that would be perfect for waking up [n129] from his deep slumber. Look for [n140] in [p22] and speak with him right away.

Name: Loud Noises
Description: As luck may have it, [n140] has just finished drafting up plans for something called a "Noise Machine". However, [n140]'s friends, [n127] and [n142], are still making parts for the gizmo. If you need to make the Noise Machine, you'll need to talk to them about how to make the parts. Your first stop is [n127] and then [n142].

Name: Part 1 (Herbal Essences)
Description: [n127] needs you to help him finish his chores so he can give you [i8023]. Without it, you won't be able to make [n140]'s Noise Machine. He needs you to collect 12 [i1116] from Florapods in [p60], 10 [i1122] from Golden Moonstalks in [p60] and 15 [i1133] from Ginseng in [p61].

Name: Part 2 (Feeling Lucky)
Description: [n142] has the [i649]. This is a very important part of [n140]'s Noise Machine. Get 13 [i1168] from [m107], 13 [i1177] from [m112] and 13 [i1152] from [m42]. Return to [n142] when you're done. When you have created the Noise Machine using the [i8507] go to [p71] to wake [n129] up.

Name: That Tired Dog
Description: [n129] wasn't really asleep but was actually looking for [n125]. He hasn't asked his close friends [n127], [n128], and [n126] about [n125]. Ask each one of them and find out where [n125] is.

Name: Chibimaru and His Cookies
Description: [n125] is locked inside his house. [n129] has an idea that could work: If you bake [n125]'s most favorite food ever, [i1841], he might wake up and come out of his house after taking a whiff of its delicious scent wafting in the air. Go to [p11] and speak with [n70].

Name: Other Options
Description: [n70]'s decided to try designing houses and she wants you to try out her very first design. Gather 15 [i1118] from Bamboo in [p60], 10 [i1030] from Beryl Rock in [p63], 10 [i1034] from Electrum Rock in [p63] and 15 [i1440] from Giant Lily in [p52]. You will need these materials to make the house. Return to her once you're done collecting.

Name: Designer Decor
Description: [n70] has come up with a couple of furniture guides. Craft [i3810] and [i3709] and show it to [n70]. She will be so happy!

Name: Wake Up, Chibimaru!
Description: Bake a batch of [i1841] and bring them to [n129]. Hopefully, this will bring [n125] out of his house.

Name: The Cookie Pirate
Description: [n125] is still asleep! The cookies didn't work but [n129] doesn't want them to go to waste. He met this fellow named [n53], the cookie pirate, in [p66]. Surely he would be able to put the cookies to good use.

Name: He Likes Cookies
Description: [n53], the self-proclaimed "cookie pirate", would like to test your baking skills. He wants you to make 3 [i1835], 3 [i1790], 3 [i1791], 3 [i1792], 3 [i1841]. If [n53] likes them enough, he'll give you one of his prized possessions.

Name: Coo-Key!
Description: The Coo-Key may look like a regular cookie, but it's actually a real key! [n53] thinks it might belong to [n125]. Head over to [p75] and see if the key works.

Name: Business As Usual
Description: [n125] is behind in all of his projects. To make up for time, he needs you to visit his four apprentices and help speed up their assignments. Speak with [n128] first since his project is the most urgent one.

Name: Chairs!
Description: Your first project is to help [n128] finish his [i3818]. You will need to collect 12 [i1251] and make 2 [i627], 2 [i1813] and 1 [i599] and finally purchase 3 [i624]. Return to [n128] when you're done. After that, talk to [n126] for your next assignment.

Name: Window Frames!
Description: Project #2 is helping [n126] finish his [i3309]. Collect 13 [i1254] and make 2 [i607], 2 [i597] and 4 [i596]. You will also need to purchase 5 [i624]. Return to [n126] when you're done. After that, talk to [n127] for your next assignment.

Name: Cabinets!
Description: Your third project is all about helping [n127] finish  [n125]'s [i3863]. You will need to collect 18 [i1255] and make 2 [i600], 10 [i597], 6 [i596]. You must also purchase 8 [i624]. Return to [n127] when you're done. After that, talk to [n129] for your next Assignment.

Name: Desks!
Description: Your last project requires you to help [n129] finish [n125]'s [i3703]. He needs you to collect 20 [i1247] and make 6 [i597], 6 [i596]. You will also need to buy 8 [i624] and 3 [i625]. Return to [n129] when you're done. When you finish the last project, return to [n125] and share the good news.

Name: Oh That Crazy Monkichi
Description: [n125]'s customer, [n137], didn't pick up his order. Take [i657] and bring it to him.

Name: How To Wake Up a Monkey
Description: [n137] won't wake up. Perhaps if you present him with 25 [i10111] and 1 [i1812], he might wake up.

Name: How To Wake Up a Monkey Pt.2
Description: You're left with resorting to crude methods: [i658] and [i595]. Get these items and return to [n137].

Name: How To Wake Up a Monkey Pt.3
Description: [n137] is STILL asleep! Return to [n125] and try to figure out a plan on how to wake him up.

Name: Monkichi's Song
Description: [n125] thinks that you'll need to play [n137]'s favorite song "Bananza" to wake him up. You should visit Sanrio Land's greatest musicians [n69], [n77] and [n66], and ask them to play the song. You need to talk to them in order so the song doesn't get mixed up. Once you complete the song, visit [n137] and try to wake him up.

Name: Closed For The Day
Description: [n143]'s bakery is temporarily shut down and [n127] is worried that the folks in [p22] will go hungry. He wants to try his paw at baking so he needs you to purchase [i8407], [i8410], [i8412],  [i8414], [i8496] and [i8500] so he can learn how to bake. Travel all over Sanrio Land and talk to the different merchants and look for the cooking guides.

Name: Sharing is Good
Description: With your help, he was able to cook up his first batch of [i662] and is really excited about it. Look for 10 players in Sanrio Land and share the treats with them.

Name: The Very First Customer
Description: Your free advertising got [n127] her first customer. Deliver [i662] to [n142].

Name: Magic Breadcrumbs
Description: [n142] found a [i663] while he was out taking a walk in [p60] and he believes that it's a clue to waking [n143] up. Go to [p60] and follow the magical breadcrumbs. If you do find anything related to [n143], go to the [p73] in [p22].

Name: Out of This World Cupcakes
Description: While sleeping, [n143] came up with an incredible recipe for [i664] that he is just itching to let [n102] and [n103] try it out. Take a batch of his cupcakes to them.

Name: An Audience with the Prince
Description: The Little Twin Stars need to speak with [n138] in [p22], but he's talking in some foreign language. Try talking to [n138] and see if you can figure out what he's trying to say.

Name: Do You Speak Jeebrish?
Description: It turns out that [n137] knows how to make an [i2141], which lets a person understand any language. The Little Twin Stars need this wand but they can't seem to find [n137]. Go find him and ask him for his help!

Name: Intergalactic
Description: [n137] needs you to collect materials for making an [i2141]. Bring [n137] the following: 2 [i646], 1 [i647], 20 [i1148] from the Golden Spore Trees in [p65], 8 [i1170] from [m108] and 5 [i1115] from Prism Rock in [p62]. Once you've collected everything, go back to [n137] and see if the thing really works!

Name: Chasing Stars
Description: You can now speak with [n138]! He explains he's  here on a mission to help [n102] and [n103] get their powers back. He needs 10 [i1104] from Malachite in [p66], 5 [i1108] from Starbright Rocks in [p61], and 16 [i1053] from Starlight Rocks because these rocks contain magical essence that [n138] will use to restore the Twins' power.

Name: Star Power
Description: Bring the [i17616] to the Twins to restore their powers.

Name: Hard Worker
Description: [n131] has been working really hard on making [i3711] for some friends. He's already pretty tired, but he still has a lot to do! If only he could have some of that tea that he used to drink with [n128], he'd surely get the energy to keep going. You should ask [n128] for help.

Name: Let's Make Tea!
Description: [n128]'s looking for the guide so you can make [i1704] for [n131]. You will need to find the following ingredients: 5 [i10156], 5 [i517], 5 [i5022], 5 [i515], 3 [i10106] while he searches for [i8494].

Name: Delicious Tea
Description: You can use the guide from [n128] to learn how to make [i1704]. Don't forget to give some to [n131], he will surely be grateful for your help!

Name: Lazy Daisy
Description: One thing that [n132] loves most when she's cozying up with a good book is a nice cup of [i1726]. She decided it's time to learn how to make some herself, and all she needs is the guide book! Would you like to try finding one for her in [p22]?

Name: Giving Back
Description: [n130] needs a couch, but since [n131] is busy making sidetables, [n132] can find no one else to help her make one. Are you willing to make a [i3846] for [n130]?

Name: Care For Some Tea?
Description: [n130] wants to have a chat with you if you have time, and is offering you some [i1845]. Would you like to get 2 cups for her from [n60]? Don't forget to hand her one of them!

Name: A Sister's Concern
Description: [n130] is worried about [n133], because he's been suffering from a sore throat recently. You should make some [i1733] to soothe his throat.

Name: Cluttered Clothes
Description: [n133] is getting ready for a performance, but as always, he's struggling to find the right things to wear in his messy pile of clothes. A wardrobe would really help him get ready for his shows. Maybe [n131] knows how to make one.

Name: Clothes Management
Description: Gather materials and build a [i3868] for [n133]. He will surely be grateful.

Name: A Bright Idea
Description: [n140] is trying to make a [i3504] that glows using a special kind of material that he found in [p65]. Unfortunately, he isn't strong enough to hang around the cranky monsters in the area. Would you like to help him retrieve the 10 [i1148] from Golden Spore Trees?

Name: Share the Light
Description: [n140] would like to share his new invention with [n125]. Help him deliver a [i3504] to [n125].

Name: The Master's Test
Description: [n125] has heard of all the nice things you've done for the Chewppies, but now he's asking you to make a [i3629] for [n134] without telling you why.  Are you willing to make it for him?

Name: Kindness and Selflessness
Description: [n134] mentioned something about a test, but you'll have to talk to [n125] again to find out what it was.

Name: Missing a Friend
Description: [n54] misses his friend [n53], and he has not heard from him since he left to become a cookie pirate. Do you want to bring [i666] to [n53]?

Name: Builder Bird
Description: [n53] needs help building a nest in his new home. He needs help gathering 10 [i1143] and 10 [i1125] from [p62] and 10 [i1132] from [p61].

Name: Heartwarming
Description: [n53] was really touched by [i666], and he wants you to bring his most prized possession back to his friend as a gift.

Name: Lost and Found
Description: [n54] lost his [i551], but he says that if anyone had found it, they would have given it to [n59] for safekeeping. Pay him a visit in the [p45], maybe someone handed it to him.

Name: The Search Continues
Description: [n59] had received reports that the [m106] at [p60] were causing some trouble recently. He needs you to try and calm them down while he looks for the [i551]. Gather 10 [i1165] and 15 [i1166], then return to [n59] when you're done.

Name: Reunited
Description: [n59] found the [i551], now it's up to you to bring it back to [n54].

Name: Kitchen Creation
Description: [n130]'s trying to come up with new recipes, and this time she wants to try using 15 [i1139]s from [p66], 5 [i1122] from [p60] and 5 [i1124]s from [p62]. Would you like to gather them for her?

Name: Kitchen Creation Pt.2
Description: [n130] is about to start on her secret recipe, but needs some basic ingredients. You should be able to buy everything in her list from the [n181].

Name: Kitchen Creation Pt.3
Description: There's something missing in [n130]'s new dish, and she thinks that some farm-grown [i10114]es and [i10138] might make the dish perfect.

Name: Creepy Crawlies
Description: [n125] loves to collect and keep bugs as pets. He needs your help collecting [i1178]s and [i1158] from [p64], and also some [i1407] from farm-grown plants for him to study.

Name: Bright and Beautiful
Description: [n126]'s collection includes bright and shiny things, and she needs your help gathering some of the rare ones! Gather some [i1113]s from [p62], [i1112]s from [p64], and [i1056]s from [p46].

Name: Under the Weather
Description: [n126] heard that [n132] isn't feeling well, and she is asking if you could find out what's wrong. Bring [i672] to [n132], maybe that will cheer her up.

Name: What's Wrong, Mint?
Description: Something's bothering [n132], and it's up to you to try and cheer her up. Remember that new dish [n130] was working on? That will probably cheer her up!

Name: Feel Better Soon!
Description: Bring [i669] dish to [n132], hopefully it will make her feel better.

Name: Grand Gesture
Description: [n128] wants to do something nice for [n132], whom he heard was feeling a little under the weather recently. Being the gentleman that he is, he thought of bringing her flowers. Help him collect 3 [i1144] from [p62], 3 [i1128] and 5 [i1129] from [p64].

Name: Grand Gesture Pt.2
Description: Now that you have the flowers, you need to turn them into a bouquet. Take the [i30012] from [n128], buy some [i641] from the [n189] and bring all of them to [n70]. Maybe she can help you make a beautiful bouquet.

Name: Grand Gesture Pt.3
Description: [n70] has everything she needs to make the bouquet, but there's just one more thing that would make it perfect. There's a special ribbon that you can only get from the [m43] in [p62]. Get one for [n70], and put the finishing touch on [n132]'s special bouquet!

Name: Grand Gesture Pt.4
Description: Time to take the [i670] to [n132]!

Name: Fiesty Firesnake
Description: The [m108] in [p61] have been acting very strange, and it's up to you to try and calm them down. Gather 25 [i1170] and bring them back to [n138] when you're done.

Name: Missing Marbles
Description: [n138] heard reports that someone took some shiny stones from [n126]'s collection. It happened a few days ago, but nobody knows who did it! Talk to [n59], he seems to have some important information regarding the case.

Name: Marble Trouble
Description: [n59] says that the [m60]s in [p63] have somehow gotten their hands on [n126]'s shiny stones. Gather 24 more [i1156]s and return them to [n126].

Name: Catching the Culprit
Description: Who do you think could have taken [n126]'s stones? Someone who lives close by, who likes pranks maybe?

Requirements.Text: "Guess who took [n126]'s stones, and talk to the prankster"

Name: More Monkey Mischief
Description: It seems [n137] was up to a lot of mischief, because he also managed to drop some pearls that belonged to [n142]. Now he needs your help getting them back from the [m40]s and [m41] from [p61], and when you've collected enough, bring them back to [n142].

Name: A Valuable Lesson
Description: While [n137] was pulling pranks on others, he dropped some of his own [i1173]s in [p65], and the [m109]s have taken them all as their own. He promised to "ease up" on the pranks if you help him get his 20 [i1173]s back.

Name: Making Amends
Description: [n137] wants to apologize to [n142] and [n126] the best way he knows how. Help him make amends by bringing them each 1 [i1173] from [n137].

Name: Eager to Learn
Description: [n140] wants to learn more about the creatures of Sanrio Land, and he needs some advice as he continues his studies. Talk to [n73] and show him [i671].

Name: Animal Research
Description: Time for [n140] to learn about [m70]s, so gather some [i1161]s, [i1163]s, and [i1162]. Return to [n73] when you're done.

Name: Animal Research Pt.2
Description: [n73] now needs you to collect items from [m111]s in [p60].

Name: Animal Research Pt.3
Description: Finally, [n73] needs you to go to [p66] to find the [m115], and also to [p62] to find the [m101]. Bring back some items from them and return to [n73] when you're done.

Name: Eager to Help
Description: Bring all the items back to [n140], along with [i671]. He will surely be thankful for your help in his studies!

Name: More Surprises From Anthony
Description: [n48] needs your help! Go see [n43] in [p10] and ask him if he has an invention that can help you find the missing key.

Name: Radar Ruckus
Description: [n43] suggests making a modified [i674] to find the missing key. [n140] in [p22] can make the [i674] for you, but you'll need to bring him the materials. He needs 12 [i649], 2 [i648], 2 [i1056], 1 [i654], 10 [i5027], and 4 [i5152].

Name: We Don't Need Acorns
Description: You now have a [i674], but it needs to be modified it so it can run on magic. [n138] in [p22] can make the adjustments for you.

Name: Time For an Upgrade
Description: [n138] can turn your [i674] into a magic-powered, key-finding machine. Collect 10 [i1159] from [m64] found in [p64], and 5 [i1181] from [p40] found in [p61].

Name: Target Locked
Description: According to the [i675], [i676] is located somewhere in the [p44] or [p45]. When you find the key, bring it back to [n48].

Name: You Gotta Jiggle It!
Description:
You've found [i676]! Hurry over to the [p211] and unlock the door! 
If something's wrong, be sure to let [n48] know as soon as possible.

Name: Dear Daniel to the Rescue!
Description: The Key didn't work! [n48]'s only hope now is [n49]. Pay him a visit in [p215] and see if he can find a way to remedy the situation.

Name: Reconstruction Required
Description: [n49] knows of a spell that can restore the magic to [n48]'s key. In order to cast the spell, you will need three special items. [n33] in [p9] can tell you how to make the first item: [i677].

Name: Special Container
Description: Before you can get started on making [i677], you'll need a [i678] to put it in. [n33], the master tailor in [p9], will teach you how to make one. You'll need 5 [i5048] from [m22] in [p36] and 15 [i629], 5 [i641]. Visit [n36] about your next assignment.

Name: Crystal Clear
Description: Now it's time to do some collecting! You need to find certain treasures of monsters and a couple of minerals so [n36] can make [i679]. You need 3 [i5101], 3 [i5002], 30 [i1000], 12 [i1002], 4 [i1012] and 4 [i1013]. When you have all these materials return to [n36].

Name: Pompom Purin Smashin'
Description: How do you make [i677]? Smash up some [i679], of course! [n37] is just the boy to help you with this task.

Name: Home Brewing
Description: It's time to get the second special item on [n49]'s list: [i681]. Talk to [n143] in [p22] to find out more.

Name: Nothing But the Purest
Description: The first ingredient you need to make [i681] is [i682]. Collect the water from the small pond in [p52]. Return to [n143] once you've picked up the [i682].

Name: Mmm... Herby
Description: The next ingredient you need to find is 4 [i683]. Go to the [p47] and gather these small herbs and bring them back to [n143].

Name: The Rarest of the Rare
Description: The next ingredient on the list is the [i684]. [n143] loves wild flowers and he knows where [i684] grow. Pick some and bring it back to [n143]. It can be found somewhere in [p61].

Name: To New York!
Description:
Something strange is going on in [p108] and it looks like you're helping out! Collect 30 [i4400] from the Jersey Ginseng and 10 [i4405] from [m316]s around the area then travel to [p108] and give them to [n412]. You'll find him at the northwest entrance.
If you're having trouble try asking a friend to help you or use Loyalty Points in the Item Mall!

Name: Pet Problems
Description: [n411] is looking for 15 [i4401]s with which to cheer up a pet; you'll find these snowflakes on Jersey Ginseng in [p56].

Name: A Sticky Situation
Description: [n412] wants to power up an old sparkler to cheer up the denizens of [p108], but gnarly roots don't make for great Cheer Essence! Go into town and buy a [i4410] so you can mush up your 30 [i4400] into 15 [i4404].

Name: Cappiness
Description: With a newly powered-up wand, you're all set to take on unhappiness face-to-face! Cheer up the [c81] around the area and come back with 10 [i4451].

Name: Pet Problems II
Description: [n411]'s pet [c95] is still sad. In New Jersey (the area north of the bridge in [p108]) you can find some [i4407] from the Frostshell growing there. Perhaps this will cheer up the poor pet.

Name: Pet Problems III
Description: It's [n411]'s last hurrah - this time you need to get 10 [i4420] from [c121] on the far side of New Jersey. That's in [p108].

Name: A Fine Collection
Description: Take your collection of vibes to [n413], and she will show you how to use them to make your Sparkler stronger. She's on the east side of New Jersey.

Name: Cheering Up
Description: [n413] wants you to show her your upgraded sparkler. To upgrade, first un-equip your sparkler and put it in your inventory. Right-click on the [i4451], but don't press OK yet! Then, right-click on your sparkler. Click OK, and voila! Talk to [n413] without equipping your new Sparkler to complete the quest.

Requirements.Text: "Combine your [i4541] with your [i4451] to get [i4542], then talk to [n413] before equipping it."

Name: Brooklyn Bound
Description: [n423] told you that [n421] is having a bad hair day and needs to be cheered up. Speak with [n421], who can be found keeping it real near the south entrance of [p108].

Name: Hanamaru's Bronxaroo?
Description: It sounds like [n416]'s in a pickle. Find him at [p57], which is to the northeast of [p108].

Name: Saving New York
Description:
The mayor of [p108] has gone bonkers and is stuck in the [p109] for being naughty. Without the mayor, the denizens of this city have become demoralized and depressed. 
Only 5 combined essences of [p108] will restore the mayor. Find the [i4621], [i4622], [i4623], [i4624], and [i4625]. [n436] and her friends will help you obtain them, so go talk to them.

Name: Time Out!
Description: You combined all the Cheer Essences of [p108]! You've got what it takes to cheer up [c133], now. Go through the [p58] and cheer up [c133], then show me evidence of his good mood!

Name: The Penguinos
Description: Cheer a [c68] using the [i2409]. Return to [n425] with any interesting information you find.

Name: Don Penguino
Description: Cheer [c69] using the [i2409]. Return to [n425] with any interesting information you find.

Name: Pochi’s Pizza Parlor
Description: Go talk to [n428] inside [p156].

Name: Choco’s Chocolatey Pizza
Description: Deliver [2433] to [n412] before the pizza turns cold. You only have about 2 minutes!

Name: Bad Hair Day
Description:
Keep it real in Brooklyn by bringing [n421] 25 [i4421] from the [c116]s milling about by the tennis courts.
You've been given a [i4539] in case you don't have a Sparkler already.

Name: Hair of the Doggie
Description:
Cheer up some Lonely Chillyhounds with a touch of fresh fragrance from your new Sparkler. Bring back the [i4415]s you find to [n421].
If you lose your Sparkler, The [n433] sells these too! ...For a price.

Name: Sparks for Sparkles
Description: Rrrr-[n419] will take your Sparklers and turn them into [i4450]s. Nothing goes to waste!

Name: A New York Minute
Description: [n423] would like to be a New Yorker and wants you to bring her a [i4497]. Whatever that is, it sounds like you really have to spend some time here!

Name: Very Important Matters
Description: [n424] is very interested in [i4496]. Whatever it is, it sounds expensive! Bring some to him.

Name: Curious Beginnings
Description:
You received a new Sparkler.
If you combine it with your [i4555], you can get a new sparkler... but it will start at level 1!
Are you curious enough to try this out? Don't do it if you're not ready! If you are, put both sparklers in your inventory and find the [n419].

Name: Curiosity Continued
Description: Incredible! You've completed the Curious Series! Show your [i4663] to [n415] to claim your prize.

Name: Zappy Cells!
Description: [n415] has lost his baseball and gained a Gadgety Doodad, but It seems to be broken - it won't stop chirping "MORE ZAPPY CELLS!". Collect 75 [i4450]s and return to [n415].

Name: Zappy Cells Part Two!
Description: [n415] has lost his baseball and gained a Gadgety Doodad, but It seems to be broken - it won't stop chirping "MORE ZAPPY CELLS!". Collect 220 [i4450] and return to [n415].

Name: Zappy Cells Part Three!
Description: [n415] has lost his baseball and gained a Gadgety Doodad, but It seems to be broken - it won't stop chirping "MORE ZAPPY CELLS!". Collect 500 [i4450] and return to [n415].

Name: Zappy Cells Part Four!
Description: [n415] has lost his baseball and gained a Gadgety Doodad, but It seems to be broken - it won't stop chirping "MORE ZAPPY CELLS!". Collect 1000 [i4450] and return to [n415].

Name: Zappy Cells Forever!
Description:
You and [n415] fixed the Gadgety Doodad! Now it's "SPREADING GOOD VIBES". [n415]'s new gadget uses up power quickly, and will need a recharge soon. Collect 500 [i4450] and return to Badtz.
You can complete this quest as many times as you want  to increase Friendship and Money.

Name: Cheering Cappy I
Description: [n436] would like you to Cheer Up the [c111] walking around, and collect their [i4591]s in return. Bring 45 back to [n436].

Name: Cheering Cappy II
Description: [n436] wants you to collect the [i4591]s from the [c111] walking around. If you cheer them up, you will receive them as gifts. Bring 65 back to [n436].

Name: Cheering Waddle I
Description: [n437] would like you to Cheer Up the dopey Waddle [c112]. Collect 75 of their [i4592] and bring them back. Who knows! Maybe some of their crazy style will rub off on [n437].

Name: Cheering Waddle II
Description: [n437] would like you to continue cheering up the [c112] and bring back 110 [i4592].

Name: Cheering Vinny I
Description: [n438] would like you to Cheer up the slick-shoed [c113] and bring back their [i4593]s. When you've collected 110, come back to [n438]!

Name: Cheering Vinny II
Description: You can never get enough shine. Cheer up more [c113] and bring back 170 [i4593] to [n438].

Name: Cheering Hobbes I
Description: The Little Twin Stars want to help cheer the [c114] that walk around [p108]. You will need to cheer up the [c114] until you get 160 [i4594]s.

Name: Cheering Hobbes II
Description: The Little Twin Stars want you to continue cheering up the [c114]. Cheer up more of them until you collect 240 [i4594]s.

Name: Cheering Oswald I
Description: Bear markets and sleepy times are about to turn around. Cheer up some [c115] and return to [n441] with their strange & mystical [i4595].

Name: Cheering Oswald II
Description: This is the last [p108]er's Quest! Cheer up more [c115] and return to [n441] with more of their appreciative [i4595].

Name: Welcome to Tokyo
Description: Welcome to [p14], adventurer! Folks from this city love games, wacky gadgets and adventures. For them, these things are a way of life and it's cool and fun and everyone should try them on their stay in this beautiful city. [n326] suggests that you visit [n327] outside the [p103]. Enjoy your stay!

Name: It's Game Time
Description: [n327] recommends going to the [p103] as it is the biggest tourist attraction in [p14].

Name: The Forgotten Camera
Description: [n327]'s friend, [n328], is also new to [p14] and is off somewhere seeing the sights. However, he forgot his camera. Since you're also new in the city, [n327] thinks that it's best that you find [n328] and give him his camera so you too will have the chance to explore.

Name: The Lost Sunglasses
Description: [n328] was having so much fun exploring [p14] that he dropped his sunglasses. He doesn't exactly know where they might be but he is positive that they are in [p14].

Name: Runaway Turtle
Description: [n328] met a boy named [n329] while exploring [p14].  [n329]'s turtle is missing and [n328], while is helping by searching for the pet as he explores the city. Talk to [n329] and see what you can do to help.

Name: Return to Kurousa if Found
Description: [n329] needs your help posting [i876] on the north, south, east, west and central part of [p14]. Come back to him when you're finished.

Requirements.Text: flag 5049 "Missing Pet Flyer in the northern part of Tokyo"
flag 5048 "Missing Pet Flyer in the southern part of Tokyo"

Name: A Turtle Found
Description: [n332] has returned to [n329]! Talk to him again to receive your reward.

Name: Item Delivery
Description: [n329] was busy making fritters for [n330] when [n332] decided to go on an adventure by himself. Now [n329] can't go and deliver [i877] because he wants to stay put in case [n332] returns. He needs you to deliver the fritter to the quirky [n330]. To find [p104], check your area map.

Name: Sushi on the Loose
Description: [n330] didn't explain much but automatically assumed that you were his new assistant. He demanded you find 10 [i878] from the [m268] in [p95].

Name: Find Kerokero Keroppi
Description: [n330] wants you to find [n327]!

Name: Find Keroppa
Description: With the sudden surge of adventurers visiting [p14], food supplies are running a little low. [n330] asked help from [n331], [n327]'s dad. [n331]'s pretty good when it comes to science. You can find [n327] in [p95].

Name: Weird Science
Description: [n331] mentioned something about a [i879] but didn't really explain what it was. He gave you a [i880] that must be delivered quickly to [n330].

Name: Sunny Side Up
Description: [n330] is being weird and mysterious, which may actually be what he is like normally... if that is the right word. He needs you to bring him 2 [i1702].

Name: The Food Gigantifier
Description: Now that [n330] is full after eating a hearty breakfast, he needs you to deliver a [i881] to [n331] to determine if it is safe to eat. This is an experimental sandwich... handle with care.

Name: That's One Serious Sandwich
Description: Although the [i881] may cause side effects, [n331] is positive that the effects are just temporary and harmless. Return the [i881] back to [n330]. The food is ready for testing!

Name: Calling All Test Subjects
Description: It seems that [n330] is so stuffed after his breakfast that he can't taste-test the [i890]. You, being his assistant, must try the experimental sandwich.

Name: Ready For Round Two?
Description: [n330] needs another round of tests. This time, eat the [i882].

Name: Passing Notes
Description: [n330] is sure he knows what the problem with the [i879] is. He has given you his notes, which you need to give to [n331] for comment.

Name: The Fix-ulator? No, Fix-itnow!
Description: [n331] has a gadget called the [i884] but he thinks he needs an upgraded version to be able to fix the [i879]. Collect 8 [i1273], 25 [i1501] and 10 [i1517] to make a [i885], 25 [i1187] and 3 [i1276] to make [i886]. You can make these items by collecting the materials and then right-clicking on the materials to combine the respective items. Finally, combine the [i885], [i886] and [i884] to make the [i887].

Name: Third Time's a Charm
Description: With the [i887] attached to the [i879], [n330] is really, really, REALLY 100% sure that it will work.

Name: Boo!
Description: [n333] met the most interesting ghost at the [p102] and he wants you to meet him too.

Name: Pearly Caper
Description: The [n333] is having problems with the naughty [m259]s in the [p102]. They keep taking the [i1188] when the [n333] told them not to. Very, very naughty! Retrieve 5 [i1188] from the [m259]s.

Name: Likes the Stones
Description: The [n339] wants to keep the [n259] happy by giving them different stones. The ghosts are being cute by not telling the [n339] exactly what they want because they like to play games. Instead, they give him riddles. This time, [n340] was able to figure out that they want a [i1546]. Luckily, they can be found from the Loess Rock in the [p102]. Mine 8 and give it to [n340].

Name: The Lost Tokens.
Description: [n335] was playing in the snow area south of  [p14] earlier. Unfortunately, she dropped her  Tokens. She's sad because she cannot play in the [p103] without her Tokens.  Make your way to the [p99], [p100] and [p101] and retrieve her tokens. They're probably frozen now so be careful!

Name: It's Snow Joke!
Description: Before you go to the snowy areas and look for [n335]'s tokens, you'll need a pair of warm mittens to make searching the snow possible. Without it, you'll never be able to find the Tokens. You will need 10 [i1503]. When you have the required items, return to [n331].

Name: Numb3rz
Description: Tell [n330] about Numb3rz.

Name: We'll Just Need a Few Things
Description: According to [n330], [n341] was built to keep the snowy areas surrounding [p14] so folks can travel around and explore. He needs to be rebuilt so you can access [p100] and [p101]. Go to the [p97] and the [p99] and collect 10 [i1508], 8 [i1514], 5 [i1534] and 3 [i1273].

Name: Bubbles For Robots?
Description: [n330] requires something called a Giant Life Bubble. You can make a [i897] by collecting 10 [i898] from soil. Sanrio Land is so bursting with life that you will spot [i898] easily once you are near them. Head to the [p99] and collect [i898]s. When you have found 10 [i898], combine them with 5 [i1534] that you get from Sapphire Rocks to make a [i897].

Name: Positronic Bubble Repair Kit
Description: [n330]'s latest invention, the [i899], will surely fix [n341]. With the robot fixed, you will now be able to access [p100] and [p101] and continue looking for [n335]'s missing Tokens.

Name: Here We Go Again...
Description: [n327] hasn't heard a peep from [n330], and he's been seeing weird things. When the lab is quiet and strange things happen, it usually means that [n330] is up to something wacky again.

Name: Double Trouble
Description: Strange things are happening in [p14]. [n327]'s been seeing weird stuff and he think that [n330] is up to something wacky again.

Requirements.Text: qflag 0 "See what [n330] is going to do"

Name: More Fritter
Description: [n330]'s curiously uncontrollable hunger is acting up again. Go ask [n329] for a fritter and bring it to [n330].

Name: The Illusionizer's Broken!
Description: [n330] says something went wrong with the [i900] and he thinks that the it did more than just copy [n329]'s fritter… it copied a whole bunch of different items! The illusions are all over [p14], causing chaos and confusion! Walk around [p14] and dispel all the illusions by touching them.

Requirements.Text: qflag 4 "Dispel the Empire State Building illusion"

Name: One Wacky Scientist is Enough
Description: [n330] wants you to thank [n327] for (possibly) saving the known universe. If [n327] hadn't asked you to go see [n330], who knows what might have happened?

Name: Missing Tunes
Description: [n342] was exploring the [p98] with her other sisters but when she left the area, she noticed that everyone else didn’t go out with her. She thinks a big, bad monster took them and she’s afraid to go back.

Name: The Secret Shortcut
Description: The [n374] in [p8] is thrilled that you're going to visit [p14]. He knows a secret shortcut that will directly take you to [p106]. From there, go north, pass through [p105] and on to [p14]. Once you reach [p14], talk to [n326] so you can be formally welcomed.

Requirements.Text: "Take the Secret Shortcut on the top right area of [p8] and find your way to [p14]."

Name: To Tokyo!
Description: The [n375] in [p22] wants you to visit [p14] and enjoy all the sights, sounds and colors. Take the path to [p106], north to [n105] and then straight to [p14]. Find [n326] so you can be formally welcomed.

Name: The Capsule Machine
Description: [n338] is so excited for you! Being new in the [p103], you'll have to know how things work around here. Look for any Capsule Machine and use the 5 tokens he gave you to start playing.  The Capsule Machine requires more luck than skill. Don't get discouraged, there are a lot of great items in the Capsule Machines!

Name: The UFO Catcher
Description: Cinnamon thinks that it's time for you to try out the UFO Catcher. Use the 10 Game Center Tokens he gave you on the UFO Catcher. Directions are pretty simple: Pick any ball you want by moving the mechanical arm. You can only move horizontally once and also once vertically. Once you've picked your desired location, press the big button for the arm to go down and grab the ball. If you're lucky enough to grab one, the arm will automatically drop the ball into the chute. If you're not able to catch a prize, you will get Game Center Tickets that you can use to spend on items sold by the [n384]. Good luck!
